owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: denotes is a relation between an entity and what it is a sign or indication of, or what specifically means.
owl:ObjectProperty.resource:example: the symbol '%' denotes a proportion in relation to a whole.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: denotes

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: has part is a transitive, reflexive and antisymmetric relation between a whole and itself or a whole and its part.
owl:ObjectProperty.resource:example: a collection of cars has as a car as a part;a car has an engine as a part; a car has a piston as a part;
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has part

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: has proper part is an antisymmetric, irreflexive (normally transitive) relation between a whole and a distinct part.
owl:ObjectProperty.resource:example: a car has an engine as a proper part; a car has a piston as a proper part;
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has proper part

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: has boundary is a mereological relation between a whole and boundary located at its periphery.
owl:ObjectProperty.resource:example: the surface of an apple is a 2D boundary of the apple.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has boundary

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: A is location of B iff the spatial region occupied by A has the spatial region occupied by B as a part. [T][R]
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: is location of

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: A contains B iff the spatial region occupied by A has the spatial region occupied by B as a part, and B is not part of A. [T]
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: contains

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: A is connected to B iff there exists a fiat, material or temporal path between A and B. [S][T]
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: is connected to

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: A is adjacent to B iff there is a small, but non-zero distance between A and B
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: is adjacent to

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: is supported by is a relation between a proposition and something that supports the truth of the assertion.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: is supported by

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: has disputing evidence is a relation between a proposition and something that disputes (does not directly support) the truth of the assertion.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: is disputed by

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: a represents b when a serves as a sign, symbol or model of b.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: represents

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: has direct part is a relation to specify a part at a particular level of granularity
owl:ObjectProperty.resource:example: a car has an engine as a direct part
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has direct part

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: cites is a relation to refer to by way of example, authority or proof.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: cites

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: A 'surrounds' B iff the A 'contains' B and A 'is adjacent to' B or A 'is directly connected to' B.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: surrounds

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: is about is a relation between an information content entity and the entity that its primary subject.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: is about

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: A relation between an information content entity and a product that it (directly/indirectly) specifies
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: specifies

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: has component part is a relation between a whole and a component part where the component is instrinsic to the whole, and loss of the part would change the kind that it is.
owl:ObjectProperty.resource:example: a human has blood as a component part
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has component part

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: describes is a relation between one entity and another entity that it provides a description (detailed account of).
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: describes

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: refers to is a relation between one entity and the entity that it makes reference to.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: refers to

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: references is a relation between one entity and the entity that it makes reference to by name, but is not described by it.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: references

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: is model of is a relation between a model (an artifact) and the entity it purports to represent.
owl:ObjectProperty.resource:example: the architect builds a model that represents the building she envisions.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: is model of

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: in relation to is a comparative relation to indicate that the instance of the class holding the relation exists in relation to another entity.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: in relation to

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: has evidence is a relation between a proposition and something that demonstrates the truth of the assertion.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has evidence

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: has evidence is a relation between a proposition and something that refutes (is incompatible with) the truth of the assertion.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: is refuted by

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: has first part is a proper part relation in which the part is the first of a set of linearly ordered parts resulting from the projection of the whole on a linear coordinate system.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has first part

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: has last part is a proper part relation in which the part is the last of a set of linearly ordered parts resulting from the projection of the whole on a linear coordinate system.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has last part

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: has ordered part of is a proper part relation in which the part is one of a set of linearly ordered parts resulting from the projection of the whole on a linear coordinate system.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has ordered part

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: has data item is a relation between a dataset and any described / referrenced entity.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: has data item

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: 'is data item in' is a relation between an entity that is described or referenced in a dataset.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: is data item in

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: A relation between two objects, in which the first object contains information that is used to produce the second object.
owl:ObjectProperty.resource:example: an open reading frame encodes a protein (it contains information that specifies the amino acid composition and topology)
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: encodes

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:description: a relation between two information content entities in which one is transcribed into (an exact or similar kind) another through some process.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: is transcribed into

owl:ObjectProperty.resource:example: a relation between two information content entities in which one is translated into (a completely different kind of entity) another through some process.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: is translated into

owl:DatatypeProperty.terms:description: A relation between a informational entity and its actual value (numeric, date, text, etc).
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: has value

owl:Class.terms:description: A plan is a set of intended actions, through which one expects to achieve a goal.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: plan

owl:Class.terms:description: A generic name is the preferred name provided by manufacturer.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: generic name

owl:Class.terms:description: A language entity implements some language specification for the visual interpretation and is part of some document.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: language entity

owl:Class.terms:description: A visual language entity is a language entity that is manifested within the spectrum of light and can be pereceived and processed by a visual system.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: visual language entity

owl:Class.terms:description: A question is a linguistic expression used to make a request for information.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: question

owl:Class.terms:description: A publication is a document that has been made available by a publisher.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: publication

owl:Class.terms:description: A record is a document containing a collection of statements about some entity.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: record

owl:Class.terms:description: A specification is a description of the essential technical attributes/requirements for an object or procedure, and may be used to determine that the object / procedure meets its requirements/attributes.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: specification

owl:Class.terms:description: An action specification is a specification composed of a sequence of instructions to achieve some objective.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: action specification

owl:Class.terms:description: Language is a language entity which is the result of encoding and decoding information through systematic creation and usage of systems of symbols, each pairing a specific sign with an intended meaning, established through social conventions
owl:Class.rdfs:label: language

owl:Class.terms:description: A book is a publication composed of a large number of entries.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: book

owl:Class.terms:description: A chapter is a document section of a book or thesis.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: chapter

owl:Class.terms:description: A character is a language symbol used to construct words.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: character

owl:Class.terms:description: A novel is a fictitious prose narrative of book length, typically representing character and action with some degree of realism.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: novel

owl:Class.terms:description: A paragraph is a self-contained unit of written discourse consisting of one or more sentences.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: paragraph

owl:Class.terms:description: A document section is a component of a document.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: document section

owl:Class.terms:description: A sentence is a grammatical unit consisting of one or more words that bear minimal syntactic relation to the words that precede or follow it.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: sentence

owl:Class.terms:description: A word is the smallest free form (an item that may be expressed in isolation with semantic or pragmatic content) in a language.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: word

owl:Class.terms:description: An identifier is a label that specifically refers to (identifies) an entity (instance/type).
owl:Class.rdfs:label: identifier

owl:Class.terms:description: A name is a label used to identify an entity.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: name

owl:Class.terms:description: A preferred name is the name that is generally used by some organization.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: preferred name

owl:Class.terms:description: A common name is a name that is commonly used.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: common name

owl:Class.terms:description: A brand name is a trademarked and marketed name of a product.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: brand name

owl:Class.terms:description: A scientific name is a name given through scientific nomenclature.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: scientific name

owl:Class.terms:description: An ontology document is a document that contains an ontology.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: ontology document

owl:Class.terms:description: A descriptor (index term, subject term, subject heading) is a term that captures the essence of the topic of a document.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: descriptor

owl:Class.terms:description: A definition is a description that succintly characterizes an entity.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: definition

owl:Class.terms:description: A description is language entity in which elements of a language (formal or natural) are used to characterize an entity.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: description

owl:Class.terms:description: A category is a class of entities having particular shared characteristics.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: category

owl:Class.terms:description: A criterion is a specification to describe properties used for evaluation.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: criterion

owl:Class.terms:description: An inclusion criterion is a criterion that must be present to satisfy some objective.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: inclusion criterion

owl:Class.terms:description: An exclusion criterion is a criterion that must be absent to satistify the objective.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: exclusion criterion

owl:Class.terms:description: A keyword is a descriptor in which the association of the word with the entity facilitates information retrieval.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: keyword

owl:Class.terms:description: A document is a bounded physical or digital representation of a body of information designed with the capacity (and usually intent) to communicate.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: document

owl:Class.terms:description: A manuscript is a document prior to publication.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: manuscript

owl:Class.terms:description: A note is a brief document.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: note

owl:Class.terms:description: A patent is an information entity granted by a patent issuing authority which confers upon the patenter the sole right to make, use and sell an invention for a set period of time.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: patent

owl:Class.terms:description: An article is a publication that is stand-alone section of a larger work.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: article

owl:Class.terms:description: A blog is a publication accessible at some website and is typically about various experiences.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: blog

owl:Class.terms:description: A book volume is a book that is part of a collection.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: book volume

owl:Class.terms:description: A conference proceedings is a book composed of papers presented at a conference.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: conference proceedings

owl:Class.terms:description: An edited publication is a publication that has been examined and potentially changed by an editor.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: edited publication

owl:Class.terms:description: A manual is a document that instructs on the usage of a device.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: manual

owl:Class.terms:description: A technical report is a publication published by a school or other institution, usually numbered within a series.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: technical report

owl:Class.terms:description: A thesis document is the written research component of a post-secondary institution that contains a statement supported by arguments.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: thesis document

owl:Class.terms:description: An honor's thesis is a thesis prepared as a requirement for an honor's undergraduate degree.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: honor's thesis

owl:Class.terms:description: A Master's thesis is a thesis prepared as a requirement for a Master's degree.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: master's thesis

owl:Class.terms:description: A PhD thesis is a thesis prepared as a requirement for a doctoral degree.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: phd thesis

owl:Class.terms:description: A booklet is a document that lacks a named publisher or sponsoring institution.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: booklet

owl:Class.terms:description: A diary is a document which describes day-to-day experiences.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: diary

owl:Class.terms:description: A bibliographic attribute is an attribute related to publications.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: document component

owl:Class.terms:description: An address is a position that indicates the physical location of some entity using a social convention.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: address

owl:Class.terms:description: A citation is a textual entity which denotes a source described in the bibliography or reference section of a document.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: citation

owl:Class.terms:description: A document title is a textual entity that summarizes the topic of the document in one sentence.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: document title

owl:Class.terms:description: A reference is a textual entity that describes a single source used in the preparation or development of the work.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: reference

owl:Class.terms:description: a label is a term that is associated with some entity
owl:Class.rdfs:label: label

owl:Class.terms:description: A language label is a label that denotes the language of a textual entity.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: language label

owl:Class.terms:description: A first name is a name that denotes a specific individual between members of a group of individuals, whose members usually share the same surname.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: first name

owl:Class.terms:description: A last name (surname) is a name added to a given name and is part of a personal name and is often the family name.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: last name

owl:Class.terms:description: A personal name is a name to identify an individual person and usually comprises of a first name and a last name.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: personal name

owl:Class.terms:description: A legal name is a name given at birth, or which appears on their birth certificate, marriage certificate, or change of name certificate.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: legal name

owl:Class.terms:description: A title is a textual entity that summarily describes some entity.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: title

owl:Class.terms:description: A document version is a version of a work in some sequence of derivative works.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: document version

owl:Class.terms:description: An abstract section is a document section that provides brief summary of a document that explains the main argument(s), topic(s) or findings.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: abstract section

owl:Class.terms:description: An acknowledgements section is a document section that identifies individuals, groups or organizations for their support in the development of the work.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: acknowledgements section

owl:Class.terms:description: An author contribution section is a document section that describes the contribution of the authors.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: author contribution section

owl:Class.terms:description: An author section is a document section that lists the contributing authors.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: author section

owl:Class.terms:description: A bibliography section is a document section that is composed of a list of references used in the development of the work.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: bibliography section

owl:Class.terms:description: A copyright section is a document section that contains a notice of copyright.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: copyright section

owl:Class.terms:description: A correspondence section is a document section that contains the details for contacting the corresponding author.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: correspondence section

owl:Class.terms:description: The discussion section is a document section containing a summary of the findings, a reflection on the significance of findings, comparison with related work, among others.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: discussion section

owl:Class.terms:description: An introduction section is a document section that generally provides background, motivation and goals of the work.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: introduction section

owl:Class.terms:description: The materials and methods section is a document section containing a description of the materials and methods used in the study.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: materials and methods section

owl:Class.terms:description: The materials section is a document section containing a description of the materials used in the study.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: materials section

owl:Class.terms:description: The methods section is a document section containing a description of the methods used in the study.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: methods section

owl:Class.terms:description: The results section is a document section describing the main findings of the study.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: results section

owl:Class.terms:description: The table of contents is a document section that lists all sections (and optionally subsections) in a sequential order along with their page number.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: table of contents

owl:Class.terms:description: A namespace label is a short name for a namespace.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: namespace label

owl:Class.terms:description: A proposition is a sentence expressing something true or false.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: proposition

owl:Class.terms:description: An argument is a set of one or more declarative sentences (or propositions) known as the premises along with another declarative sentence (or proposition) known as the conclusion.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: argument

owl:Class.terms:description: A premise is a proposition of an argument from which the conclusion is drawn.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: premise

owl:Class.terms:description: A conclusion is a proposition which is reached after considering the evidence, arguments or premises.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: conclusion

owl:Class.terms:description: A deductive argument is an argument that asserts that the truth of the conclusion is a logical consequence of the premises.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: deductive argument

owl:Class.terms:description: An inductive argument is an argument that asserts that the truth of the conclusion is supported by the premises.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: inductive argument

owl:Class.terms:description: A sound argument is a valid argument with true premises.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: sound argument

owl:Class.terms:description: A valid argument is an argument where the truth of the conclusion is a logical consequence of the premises and (consequently) its corresponding conditional is a necessary truth.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: valid argument

owl:Class.terms:description: An invalid argument is an argument where the truth of the conclusion is false because it is not a logical consequence of the premises.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: invalid argument

owl:Class.terms:description: A term is a word or phrase used to denote one or more entities.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: term

owl:Class.terms:description: A hypothesis is a proposed explanation for a phenomenon.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: hypothesis

owl:Class.terms:description: An excerpt is a contiguous or discontiguous portion of a document.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: excerpt

owl:Class.terms:description: A quote is a excerpt that is attributed to a particular source.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: quote

owl:Class.terms:description: A web page is a document that is published according to World Wide Web standards.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: web page

owl:Class.terms:description: Email message is a digital document that is composed of a header and a body and is transmitted using the SMTP protocol.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: email

owl:Class.terms:description: A letter is a document that contains a personal communication from one part to another.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: letter

owl:Class.terms:description: A functional specification is a specification that describes the characteristics of an object.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: functional specification

owl:Class.terms:description: A design specification is a specification that provides precise and explicit information about the requirements for a product design.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: design specification

owl:Class.terms:description: A specification for spatial location is an effective specification towards representation spatial position or spatial data.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: spatial specification

owl:Class.terms:description: A coordinate system is a specification for spatial location that uses a set of numbers, or coordinates, to uniquely determine the position of a point or other geometric element.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: coordinate system

owl:Class.terms:description: A Cartesian coordinate system specifies each point uniquely in a plane by a pair of numerical coordinates, which are the signed distances from the point to two fixed perpendicular directed lines, measured in the same unit of length.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: cartesian coordinate system

owl:Class.terms:description: A concept is term that refers to a generalization of a set of attributes or entities.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: concept

owl:Class.terms:description: A polar coordinate system is a two-dimensional coordinate system in which each point on a plane is determined by a distance from a fixed point and an angle from a fixed direction.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: polar coordinate system

owl:Class.terms:description: A positional description is a description of location using some system or frame of reference.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: positional identifier

owl:Class.terms:description: A cylindrical coordinate system is a three-dimensional coordinate system that specifies point positions by the distance from a chosen reference axis, the direction from the axis relative to a chosen reference direction, and the distance from a chosen reference plane perpendicular to the axis.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: cylindrical coordinate system

owl:Class.terms:description: A spherical coordinate system is a coordinate system for three-dimensional space where the position of a point is specified by three numbers: the radial distance of that point from a fixed origin, its polar angle measured from a fixed zenith direction, and the azimuth angle of its orthogonal projection on a reference plane that passes through the origin and is orthogonal to the zenith, measured from a fixed reference direction on that plane.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: spherical coordinate system

owl:Class.terms:description: An OWL ontology is an ontology as specified by the W3C OWL specification.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: OWL ontology

owl:Class.terms:description: An objective is a proposition that indicates a planned or anticipated outcome.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: objective

owl:Class.terms:description: purpose is the reason for which something is done or created or for which something exists.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: purpose

owl:Class.terms:description: A belief is a proposition that is believed to be true.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: belief

owl:Class.terms:description: A primary title is a title that should be first used in describing some entity.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: primary title

owl:Class.terms:description: A secondary title is a title of lesser importance that should be used after the first title in describing some entity.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: secondary title

owl:Class.terms:description: A primary graph title is a primary title that describes a statistical graph.
owl:Class.resource:example: "Total value of permits increased slightly in December" in Graph 1 of http://tinyurl.com/opwnvm
owl:Class.rdfs:label: primary graph title

owl:Class.terms:description: A secondary graph title is a secondary title that describes a statistical graph.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: secondary graph title

owl:Class.terms:description: A phrase is a group of words functioning as a single unit in the syntax of a sentence.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: phrase

owl:Class.terms:description: A clause consists of a subject and a predicate.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: clause

owl:Class.terms:description: An idea is a proposition about some object of conceptual thought.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: idea

owl:Class.terms:description: structure is the specification that refers to the composition and arrangement of parts of an object.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: structure

owl:Class.terms:description: A standard is a socially-agreed upon specification.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: standard

owl:Class.terms:description: A formal specification is a mathematical description of software or hardware that may be used to develop an implementation.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: formal specification

owl:Class.terms:description: An RDFS ontology is an ontology that conforms to the syntax and semantics of the Resource Description Framework Schema (RDFS).
owl:Class.rdfs:label: RDFS ontology

owl:Class.terms:description: An OBO ontology is an ontology document as specified by the Open Biological Ontology community.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: OBO ontology

owl:Class.terms:description: chemical structure is the structure of a chemical entity in terms of its molecular geometry and electronic structure.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: chemical structure

owl:Class.terms:description: molecular structure is the spatial arrangement of atoms in a molecule and the chemical bonds that hold the atoms together.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: molecular structure

owl:Class.terms:description: A textual entity is language entity that is manifested as a sequence of one or more distinct characters.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: textual entity

owl:Class.terms:description: A version label is a label for a particular form or variation of an earlier or original type.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: version label

owl:Class.terms:description: A software version label is a version label for a piece of software.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: software version label

owl:Class.terms:description: A unique identifier is an identifier that uniquely identifies some thing.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: unique identifier

owl:Class.terms:description: A justification is a proposition that defends, explains or excuses some argument.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: justification

owl:Class.terms:description: A specification of an object, manifested by an agent, intended to accomplish goals, in a particular environment, using a set of primitive components, satisfying a set of requirements, subject to constraints.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: design

owl:Class.terms:description: A chemical identifier is an identifier for a chemical entity
owl:Class.rdfs:label: chemical identifier

owl:Class.terms:description: A record identifier is an identifier for a database entry.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: record identifier

owl:Class.terms:description: A physical entity identifier is an identifier for a physical entity.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: physical entity identifier

owl:Class.terms:description: An informational entity identifier is an identifier for an informational entity.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: informational entity identifier

owl:Class.terms:description: A molecular identifier is an identifier for a molecular entity.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: molecular identifier

owl:Class.terms:description: A street name is the token given to identify a particular street.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: street name

owl:Class.terms:description: An apartment number is the number assigned to identify an apartment in a building of apartments.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: apartment number

owl:Class.terms:description: A versioned record is a record for which there exists another variant based that was derived via modification of the facts.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: versioned record

owl:Class.terms:description: An answer is a reply to a question.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: answer

owl:Class.terms:description: A verbal language entity is a language entity that is manifested through sound.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: verbal language entity

owl:Class.terms:description: A Uniform Resource Locator or Universal Resource Locator (URL) is a specific character string that constitutes a reference to an Internet resource.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: URL

owl:Class.terms:description: A measurement scale is a functional specification that specifies an allowed range of categories or values.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: measurement scale

owl:Class.terms:description: A nominal scale of measurement only specifies a limited set of categories.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: nomimal scale

owl:Class.terms:description: A binary scale is a measurement scale that specifies a choice between two values.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: binary scale

owl:Class.terms:description: A numeric scale of measurement is one that only specifies numeric values.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: numeric scale

owl:Class.terms:description: A decimal scale of measurement is one that only specifies decimal values.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: decimal scale

owl:Class.terms:description: An integer scale of measurement is one that only specifies integer values.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: integer scale

owl:Class.terms:description: A numeric label is a number used as a label.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: numeric label

owl:Class.terms:description: A standard operating procedure is a specification approved for use in specific environments.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: standard operating procedure

owl:Class.terms:description: A syllable is a verbal entity of language having one vowel sound, with or without surrounding consonants, forming the whole or a part of a word.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: syllable

owl:Class.terms:description: A consonant is a verbal entity of language that is articulated with complete or partial closure of the vocal tract.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: consonant

owl:Class.terms:description: A vowel is a verbal entity of language that is pronounced with an open vocal tract so that there is no build-up of air pressure at any point above the glottis.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: vowel

owl:Class.terms:description: A sign language (also signed language) is a language that involves manual communication and body language to convey meaning. This can involve simultaneously combining hand shapes, orientation and movement of the hands, arms or body, and facial expressions to fluidly express a speaker's thoughts.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: sign language

owl:Class.terms:description: A verbal language is a language that uses sounds to communicate.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: verbal language

owl:Class.terms:description: written language is a language that is communicated through a writing system.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: written language

owl:Class.terms:description: A diagnostic opinion is an opinion resulting from a medical diagnostic procedure.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: diagnostic opinion

owl:Class.terms:description: An opinion is a belief that is the result of emotion or interpretation of facts.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: opinion

owl:Class.terms:description: A syndrome is composed of a set of several clinically recognizable features, signs (observed by someone other than the patient), symptoms (reported by the patient), phenomena or characteristics that often occur together.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: syndrome

owl:Class.terms:description: A prognosis is a proposition about the likely course of a disease, the chance of recovery or recurrence.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: prognosis

owl:Class.terms:description: A report is a textual document made that present focused, salient content to a specific audience.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: report

owl:Class.terms:description: A medical health record is a record of a single patient's medical history.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: medical health record

owl:Class.terms:description: A medical report is a report prepared by a health care practioner about test outcomes or health status of an individual.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: medical report

owl:Class.terms:description: A peer reviewed article is an article that has undergone peer-review and deemed acceptable for publication.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: peer reviewed article

owl:Class.terms:description: A major version number is a version of a software that exhibits a significant change in functionalilty from a prior version.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: major version number

owl:Class.terms:description: A minor version number is a version of a software that exhibits minor features or significant fix from a prior version.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: minor version number

owl:Class.terms:description: A revision number is a version of a software in which bugs have been fixed from a prior version.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: revision number

owl:Class.terms:description: A morpheme is the smallest semantically meaningful unit in a language.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: morpheme

owl:Class.terms:description: A study design is a protocol for the proper execution of a study which normally requires a carefullly crafted research question or hypothesis and at least one variable under observation and observed values for that variable.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: study design

owl:Class.terms:description: A recipe is a set of instructions that describe how to prepare or make something.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: recipe

owl:Class.terms:description: An experimental protocol is an action specification with respect to the design and implementation of experiments. In addition to providing a detailed set of procedures and lists of required equipment and instruments, experimental protocols often include information on safety precautions, the calculation of results and reporting standards, including statistical analysis and rules for predefining and documenting excluded data to avoid bias.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: experimental protocol

owl:Class.terms:description: A reason is a justification that specifies the motive for an action or a determination.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: reason

owl:Class.terms:description: speculation is an opinion based on incomplete evidence.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: speculation

owl:Class.terms:description: A text span is a subset of contiguous sequence of characters of a textual entity.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: text span

owl:Class.terms:description: A microarray probe set identifier is an identifier for a set of probe pairs selected to represent expressed sequences on an array.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: microarray probe set identifier

owl:Class.terms:description: A genotype is a functional specification of a biological entity in terms of its genetic composition (or lack thereof).
owl:Class.rdfs:label: genotype

owl:Class.terms:description: A vocabulary is a collection of terms.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: vocabulary

owl:Class.terms:description: electronic structure is the electron configuration is the distribution of electrons of an atom or molecule (or other physical structure) in atomic or molecular orbitals.
owl:Class.resource:example: the electron configuration of the neon atom is 1s2 2s2 2p6.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: electronic structure

owl:Class.terms:description: A crystal structure is the arrangement of atoms or molecules in a crystalline liquid or solid.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: crystal structure

owl:Class.terms:description: A pathway is an effective specification that outlines a set of actions that forms a way to achieve an objective.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: pathway

owl:Class.terms:description: An annotation is a written explanatory or critical description, or other in-context information (e.g., pattern, motif, link), that has been associated with data or other types of information.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: annotation

owl:Class.terms:description: A comment is a verbal or written remark often related to an added piece of information, or an observation or statement.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: comment

owl:Class.terms:description: An issue is a single instance of a periodically published journal, magazine, or newspaper.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: issue

owl:Class.terms:description: A statement is a proposition that is either (a) a meaningful declarative sentence that is either true or false, or (b) that which a true or false declarative sentence asserts.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: statement

owl:Class.terms:description: A software process identifier is an identifier for a software process in some operating system.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: software process identifier

owl:Class.terms:description: history is a sequence of past events.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: history

owl:Class.terms:description: a pharmacokinetic pathway is a metabolic pathway which describes the metabolism of a drug molecule.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: pharmacokinetic pathway

owl:Class.terms:description: a pharmacodynamic pathay is a regulatory pathway in which a drug molecule regulates the activity of one or more components organized in a pathway.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: pharmacodynamic pathway

owl:Class.terms:description: a middle name is a name assigned to an individual that is not the first or last name.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: middle name

owl:Class.terms:description: a middle initial is an abbreviated middle name.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: middle initial

owl:Class.terms:description: a telephone number is an identifier used to connect to a physical device capable of transfering voice or data over a network.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: telephone number

owl:Class.terms:description: a cellular phone number is a number to connect to a mobile device
owl:Class.rdfs:label: cellular phone number

owl:Class.terms:description: a fax number is a number to connect to fax device
owl:Class.rdfs:label: fax number

owl:Class.terms:description: an IP number is an number to connect to a device on the internet.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: IP number

owl:Class.terms:description: an email address is an identifier to send mail to particular electronic mailbox.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: email address

owl:Class.terms:description: a work phone number is the number to connect to an phone at a place of work.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: work phone number

owl:Class.terms:description: a home phone number is the number to connect to an phone at a place of residence.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: home phone number

owl:Class.terms:description: A diagnosis is the result of a medical investigation to identify a disorder from its signs and symptoms.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: diagnosis

owl:Class.terms:description: A statute is a formal written enactment of a legislative authority that governs a state, city or country.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: statute

owl:Class.terms:description: A legal document proposing or enacting a law or a group of laws.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: legislation

owl:Class.terms:description: A legal document is a formally executed written document that can be formally attributed to its author, records and formally expresses a legally enforceable act, process, or contractual duty, obligation, or right, and therefore evidences that act, process, or agreement.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: legal document

owl:Class.terms:description: A brief is a written legal document used in various legal adversarial systems that is presented to a court arguing why one party to a particular case should prevail.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: brief

owl:Class.terms:description: A bill is proposed legislation under consideration by a legislature.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: bill

owl:Class.dc:description: a gene symbol is a short name assigned to a gene.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: gene symbol

owl:Class.dc:description: a statement of consequence is a statement concerning the result or effect of an action or condition.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: statement of consequence

owl:Class.dc:description: a notation is a series or system of written symbols used to represent numbers, amounts, or elements.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: notation

owl:Class.dc:description: a notation to describe a chemical entity
owl:Class.rdfs:label: chemical notation

owl:Class.dc:description: The HGVS (human genome variation society) notation is a notation to specify a sequence variation in dna, rna, proteins, and other biomolecules.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: hgvs notation

owl:Class.dc:description: an ontology is a formal specification of entities, their attributes and relationships.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: ontology

owl:Class.dc:description: evidence is the body of facts or information indicating whether a belief or proposition is true or valid.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: evidence

owl:Class.dc:description: A terminology is a set of terms used for a specified application.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: terminology

owl:Class.terms:description: A PDB chain identifier is a alphabetical label to identify a molecule in a structure provided by the Protein DataBank .
owl:Class.rdfs:label: PDB chain identifier

owl:Class.terms:description: A PDB record identifier is an identifier for a PDB generated record.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: PDB record identifier

owl:Class.terms:description: evolutionary lineage is a sequence of species, that form a line of descent, each new species the direct result of speciation from an immediate ancestral species.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: evolutionary lineage

owl:Class.terms:description: family history is the systematic narrative and research of past events relating to a specific family, or specific families.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: family history

owl:Class.terms:description: A biochemical pathway specifies a series of biochemical modifications and transformations towards achieving some biological outcome.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: biochemical pathway

owl:Class.terms:description: A chemical reaction pathway specifies a series of chemical reactions towards producing some chemical product.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: chemical reaction pathway

owl:Class.terms:description: A chemical synthesis pathway is a pathway involved in the assembly of a chemical.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: chemical synthesis pathway

owl:Class.terms:description: A chemical degradation pathway is a pathway involved in the disassembly of a chemical.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: chemical degradation pathway

owl:Class.terms:description: A metabolic pathway is a series of biochemical reactions that begins with one or more substrates and ends with one or more products.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: metabolic pathway

owl:Class.terms:description: A regulatory pathway is a series of biochemical reactions that lead to the increase or decrease of activity of participating molecular components.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: regulatory pathway

owl:Class.terms:description: A medical history is a record of the events of a recipient of medical care.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: medical history
